{"type": "USJ", "version": "3.1", "content": [{"type": "book", "marker": "id", "content": ["46-1CO-web.sfm English Arabic Names Version (EANV)"], "code": "1CO"}, {"type": "para", "marker": "ide", "content": ["UTF-8\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "h", "content": ["1 Corinthians \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "toc1", "content": ["Paul\u2019s First Letter to the Corinthians \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "toc2", "content": ["1 Corinthians \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "toc3", "content": ["1Co \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "mt1", "content": ["Paul\u2019s First Letter to the Corinthians \n"]}, {"type": "chapter", "marker": "c", "number": "1", "sid": "1CO 1"}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "1", "sid": "1CO 1:1"}, "Paul, called to be an apostle of Al Masih Isa through the will of Allah, and our brother Sosthenes,\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "2", "sid": "1CO 1:2"}, "to the assembly of Allah which is at Corinth\u2014those who are sanctified in Masih Isa, called saints, with all who call on\nthe name of our Lord Al Masih Isa in every place, both theirs and ours:\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "3", "sid": "1CO 1:3"}, "Grace to you and peace from Allah our Father and the Lord Al Masih Isa.\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "4", "sid": "1CO 1:4"}, "I always thank my Allah concerning you, for the grace of Allah which was given you in Masih Isa;\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "5", "sid": "1CO 1:5"}, "that in everything you were enriched in him, in all speech and all knowledge;\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "6", "sid": "1CO 1:6"}, "even as the testimony of Masih was confirmed in you: \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "7", "sid": "1CO 1:7"}, "so that you come behind in no gift; waiting for the revelation of our Lord Al Masih Isa;\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "8", "sid": "1CO 1:8"}, "who will also confirm you until the end, blameless in the day of our Lord Al Masih Isa.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "9", "sid": "1CO 1:9"}, "Allah is faithful, through whom you were called into the fellowship of his Son, Al Masih Isa, our Lord.\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "10", "sid": "1CO 1:10"}, "Now I beg you, brothers,", {"type": "note", "marker": "f", "content": ["  ", {"type": "char", "marker": "fr", "content": ["1:10 "]}, {"type": "char", "marker": "ft", "content": ["The word for \u201cbrothers\u201d here and where context allows may also be correctly\ntranslated \u201cbrothers and sisters\u201d or \u201csiblings.\u201d"]}], "caller": "+"}, " through the name of our Lord, Al Masih Isa, that you all speak the same\nthing, and that there be no divisions amongst you, but that you be perfected together in the same mind and in the same\njudgement. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "11", "sid": "1CO 1:11"}, "For it has been reported to me concerning you, my brothers, by those who are from Chloe\u2019s household, that there are\ncontentions amongst you. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "12", "sid": "1CO 1:12"}, "Now I mean this, that each one of you says, \u201cI follow Paul,\u201d \u201cI follow Apollos,\u201d \u201cI follow Cephas,\u201d and, \u201cI follow\nMasih.\u201d \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "13", "sid": "1CO 1:13"}, "Is Masih divided? Was Paul crucified for you? Or were you baptised into the name of Paul?\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "14", "sid": "1CO 1:14"}, "I thank Allah that I baptised none of you, except Crispus and Gaius,\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "15", "sid": "1CO 1:15"}, "so that no one should say that I had baptised you into my own name.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "16", "sid": "1CO 1:16"}, "(I also baptised the household of Stephanas; besides them, I don\u2019t know whether I baptised any other.)\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "17", "sid": "1CO 1:17"}, "For Masih sent me not to baptise, but to preach the Good News\u2014not in wisdom of words, so that the cross of Masih wouldn\u2019t\nbe made void. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "18", "sid": "1CO 1:18"}, "For the word of the cross is foolishness to those who are dying, but to us who are being saved it is the power of Allah.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "19", "sid": "1CO 1:19"}, "For it is written, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": ["\u201cI will destroy the wisdom of the wise. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["I will bring the discernment of the discerning to nothing.\u201d", {"type": "note", "marker": "x", "content": [{"type": "char", "marker": "xo", "content": ["1:19 "]}, {"type": "char", "marker": "xt", "content": ["Isaiah 29:14"]}], "caller": "+"}, " \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "20", "sid": "1CO 1:20"}, "Where is the wise? Where is the scribe? Where is the lawyer of this world? Hasn\u2019t Allah made foolish the wisdom of this\nworld? \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "21", "sid": "1CO 1:21"}, "For seeing that in the wisdom of Allah, the world through its wisdom didn\u2019t know Allah, it was Allah\u2019s good pleasure\nthrough the foolishness of the preaching to save those who believe.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "22", "sid": "1CO 1:22"}, "For Jews ask for signs, Greeks seek after wisdom, \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "23", "sid": "1CO 1:23"}, "but we preach Masih crucified: a stumbling block to Jews, and foolishness to Greeks,\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "24", "sid": "1CO 1:24"}, "but to those who are called, both Jews and Greeks, Masih is the power of Allah and the wisdom of Allah;\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "25", "sid": "1CO 1:25"}, "because the foolishness of Allah is wiser than men, and the weakness of Allah is stronger than men.\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "26", "sid": "1CO 1:26"}, "For you see your calling, brothers, that not many are wise according to the flesh, not many mighty, and not many noble;\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "27", "sid": "1CO 1:27"}, "but Allah chose the foolish things of the world that he might put to shame those who are wise. Allah chose the weak\nthings of the world that he might put to shame the things that are strong.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "28", "sid": "1CO 1:28"}, "Allah chose the lowly things of the world, and the things that are despised, and the things that don\u2019t exist, that he\nmight bring to nothing the things that exist, \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "29", "sid": "1CO 1:29"}, "that no flesh should boast before Allah. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "30", "sid": "1CO 1:30"}, "Because of him, you are in Masih Isa, who was made to us wisdom from Allah, and righteousness and sanctification, and\nredemption: \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "31", "sid": "1CO 1:31"}, "that, as it is written, \u201cHe who boasts, let him boast in the\nLord.\u201d", {"type": "note", "marker": "x", "content": [{"type": "char", "marker": "xo", "content": ["1:31 "]}, {"type": "char", "marker": "xt", "content": ["Jeremiah 9:24"]}], "caller": "+"}, " \n"]}, {"type": "chapter", "marker": "c", "number": "2", "sid": "1CO 2"}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "1", "sid": "1CO 2:1"}, "When I came to you, brothers, I didn\u2019t come with excellence of speech or of wisdom, proclaiming to you the testimony of\nAllah. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "2", "sid": "1CO 2:2"}, "For I determined not to know anything amongst you except Al Masih Isa and him crucified.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "3", "sid": "1CO 2:3"}, "I was with you in weakness, in fear, and in much trembling.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "4", "sid": "1CO 2:4"}, "My speech and my preaching were not in persuasive words of human wisdom, but in demonstration of the Spirit and of power,\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "5", "sid": "1CO 2:5"}, "that your faith wouldn\u2019t stand in the wisdom of men, but in the power of Allah.\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "6", "sid": "1CO 2:6"}, "We speak wisdom, however, amongst those who are full grown, yet a wisdom not of this world nor of the rulers of this world\nwho are coming to nothing. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "7", "sid": "1CO 2:7"}, "But we speak Allah\u2019s wisdom in a mystery, the wisdom that has been hidden, which Allah foreordained before the worlds for\nour glory, \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "8", "sid": "1CO 2:8"}, "which none of the rulers of this world has known. For had they known it, they wouldn\u2019t have crucified the Lord of glory.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "9", "sid": "1CO 2:9"}, "But as it is written, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": ["\u201cThings which an eye didn\u2019t see, and an ear didn\u2019t hear, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["which didn\u2019t enter into the heart of man, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["these Allah has prepared for those who love him.\u201d", {"type": "note", "marker": "x", "content": [{"type": "char", "marker": "xo", "content": ["2:9\n"]}, {"type": "char", "marker": "xt", "content": ["Isaiah 64:4"]}], "caller": "+"}, " \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "10", "sid": "1CO 2:10"}, "But to us, Allah revealed them through the Spirit. For the Spirit searches all things, yes, the deep things of Allah.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "11", "sid": "1CO 2:11"}, "For who amongst men knows the things of a man, except the spirit of the man, which is in him? Even so, no one knows the\nthings of Allah, except Allah\u2019s Spirit. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "12", "sid": "1CO 2:12"}, "But we received not the spirit of the world, but the Spirit which is from Allah, that we might know the things that were\nfreely given to us by Allah. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "13", "sid": "1CO 2:13"}, "We also speak these things, not in words which man\u2019s wisdom teaches, but which the Holy Spirit teaches, comparing\nspiritual things with spiritual things. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "14", "sid": "1CO 2:14"}, "Now the natural man doesn\u2019t receive the things of Allah\u2019s Spirit, for they are foolishness to him, and he can\u2019t know\nthem, because they are spiritually discerned. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "15", "sid": "1CO 2:15"}, "But he who is spiritual discerns all things, and he himself is judged by no one.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "16", "sid": "1CO 2:16"}, "\u201cFor who has known the mind of the Lord, that he should instruct him?\u201d\n", {"type": "note", "marker": "x", "content": [{"type": "char", "marker": "xo", "content": ["2:16 "]}, {"type": "char", "marker": "xt", "content": ["Isaiah 40:13"]}], "caller": "+"}, " But we have Masih\u2019s mind. \n"]}, {"type": "chapter", "marker": "c", "number": "3", "sid": "1CO 3"}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "1", "sid": "1CO 3:1"}, "Brothers, I couldn\u2019t speak to you as to spiritual, but as to fleshly, as to babies in Masih.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "2", "sid": "1CO 3:2"}, "I fed you with milk, not with meat; for you weren\u2019t yet ready. Indeed, you aren\u2019t ready even now,\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "3", "sid": "1CO 3:3"}, "for you are still fleshly. For insofar as there is jealousy, strife, and factions amongst you, aren\u2019t you fleshly, and\ndon\u2019t you walk in the ways of men? \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "4", "sid": "1CO 3:4"}, "For when one says, \u201cI follow Paul,\u201d and another, \u201cI follow Apollos,\u201d aren\u2019t you fleshly?\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "5", "sid": "1CO 3:5"}, "Who then is Apollos, and who is Paul, but servants through whom you believed, and each as the Lord gave to him?\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "6", "sid": "1CO 3:6"}, "I planted. Apollos watered. But Allah gave the increase. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "7", "sid": "1CO 3:7"}, "So then neither he who plants is anything, nor he who waters, but Allah who gives the increase.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "8", "sid": "1CO 3:8"}, "Now he who plants and he who waters are the same, but each will receive his own reward according to his own labour.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "9", "sid": "1CO 3:9"}, "For we are Allah\u2019s fellow workers. You are Allah\u2019s farming, Allah\u2019s building.\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "10", "sid": "1CO 3:10"}, "According to the grace of Allah which was given to me, as a wise master builder I laid a foundation, and another builds\non it. But let each man be careful how he builds on it. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "11", "sid": "1CO 3:11"}, "For no one can lay any other foundation than that which has been laid, which is Al Masih Isa.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "12", "sid": "1CO 3:12"}, "But if anyone builds on the foundation with gold, silver, costly stones, wood, hay, or stubble,\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "13", "sid": "1CO 3:13"}, "each man\u2019s work will be revealed. For the Day will declare it, because it is revealed in fire; and the fire itself will\ntest what sort of work each man\u2019s work is. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "14", "sid": "1CO 3:14"}, "If any man\u2019s work remains which he built on it, he will receive a reward.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "15", "sid": "1CO 3:15"}, "If any man\u2019s work is burnt, he will suffer loss, but he himself will be saved, but as through fire.\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "16", "sid": "1CO 3:16"}, "Don\u2019t you know that you are a temple of Allah, and that Allah\u2019s Spirit lives in you?\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "17", "sid": "1CO 3:17"}, "If anyone destroys Allah\u2019s temple, Allah will destroy him; for Allah\u2019s temple is holy, which you are.\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "18", "sid": "1CO 3:18"}, "Let no one deceive himself. If anyone thinks that he is wise amongst you in this world, let him become a fool, that he\nmay become wise. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "19", "sid": "1CO 3:19"}, "For the wisdom of this world is foolishness with Allah. For it is written, \u201cHe has taken the wise in their\ncraftiness.\u201d", {"type": "note", "marker": "x", "content": [{"type": "char", "marker": "xo", "content": ["3:19 "]}, {"type": "char", "marker": "xt", "content": ["Ayyub 5:13"]}], "caller": "+"}, " \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "20", "sid": "1CO 3:20"}, "And again, \u201cThe Lord knows the reasoning of the wise, that it is\nworthless.\u201d", {"type": "note", "marker": "x", "content": [{"type": "char", "marker": "xo", "content": ["3:20 "]}, {"type": "char", "marker": "xt", "content": ["Zabur 94:11"]}], "caller": "+"}, " \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "21", "sid": "1CO 3:21"}, "Therefore let no one boast in men. For all things are yours,\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "22", "sid": "1CO 3:22"}, "whether Paul, or Apollos, or Cephas, or the world, or life, or death, or things present, or things to come. All are\nyours, \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "23", "sid": "1CO 3:23"}, "and you are Masih\u2019s, and Masih is Allah\u2019s. \n"]}, {"type": "chapter", "marker": "c", "number": "4", "sid": "1CO 4"}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "1", "sid": "1CO 4:1"}, "So let a man think of us as Masih\u2019s servants, and stewards of Allah\u2019s mysteries.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "2", "sid": "1CO 4:2"}, "Here, moreover, it is required of stewards that they be found faithful.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "3", "sid": "1CO 4:3"}, "But with me it is a very small thing that I should be judged by you, or by man\u2019s judgement. Yes, I don\u2019t judge my own\nself. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "4", "sid": "1CO 4:4"}, "For I know nothing against myself. Yet I am not justified by this, but he who judges me is the Lord.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "5", "sid": "1CO 4:5"}, "Therefore judge nothing before the time, until the Lord comes, who will both bring to light the hidden things of darkness,\nand reveal the counsels of the hearts. Then each man will get his praise from Allah.\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "6", "sid": "1CO 4:6"}, "Now these things, brothers, I have in a figure transferred to myself and Apollos for your sakes, that in us you might\nlearn not to think beyond the things which are written, that none of you be puffed up against one another.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "7", "sid": "1CO 4:7"}, "For who makes you different? And what do you have that you didn\u2019t receive? But if you did receive it, why do you boast as\nif you had not received it? \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "8", "sid": "1CO 4:8"}, "You are already filled. You have already become rich. You have come to reign without us. Yes, and I wish that you did\nreign, that we also might reign with you. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "9", "sid": "1CO 4:9"}, "For, I think that Allah has displayed us, the apostles, last of all, like men sentenced to death. For we are made a\nspectacle to the world, both to angels and men. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "10", "sid": "1CO 4:10"}, "We are fools for Masih\u2019s sake, but you are wise in Masih. We are weak, but you are strong. You have honour, but we have\ndishonour. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "11", "sid": "1CO 4:11"}, "Even to this present hour we hunger, thirst, are naked, are beaten, and have no certain dwelling place.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "12", "sid": "1CO 4:12"}, "We toil, working with our own hands. When people curse us, we bless. Being persecuted, we endure.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "13", "sid": "1CO 4:13"}, "Being defamed, we entreat. We are made as the filth of the world, the dirt wiped off by all, even until now.\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "14", "sid": "1CO 4:14"}, "I don\u2019t write these things to shame you, but to admonish you as my beloved children.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "15", "sid": "1CO 4:15"}, "For though you have ten thousand tutors in Masih, you don\u2019t have many fathers. For in Masih Isa, I became your father\nthrough the Good News. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "16", "sid": "1CO 4:16"}, "I beg you therefore, be imitators of me. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "17", "sid": "1CO 4:17"}, "Because of this I have sent Timothy to you, who is my beloved and faithful child in the Lord, who will remind you of my\nways which are in Masih, even as I teach everywhere in every assembly.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "18", "sid": "1CO 4:18"}, "Now some are puffed up, as though I were not coming to you.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "19", "sid": "1CO 4:19"}, "But I will come to you shortly, if the Lord is willing. And I will know, not the word of those who are puffed up, but the\npower. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "20", "sid": "1CO 4:20"}, "For Allah\u2019s Kingdom is not in word, but in power. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "21", "sid": "1CO 4:21"}, "What do you want? Shall I come to you with a rod, or in love and a spirit of gentleness?\n"]}, {"type": "chapter", "marker": "c", "number": "5", "sid": "1CO 5"}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "1", "sid": "1CO 5:1"}, "It is actually reported that there is sexual immorality amongst you, and such sexual immorality as is not even named\namongst the Gentiles, that one has his father\u2019s wife. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "2", "sid": "1CO 5:2"}, "You are arrogant, and didn\u2019t mourn instead, that he who had done this deed might be removed from amongst you.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "3", "sid": "1CO 5:3"}, "For I most certainly, as being absent in body but present in spirit, have already, as though I were present, judged him\nwho has done this thing. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "4", "sid": "1CO 5:4"}, "In the name of our Lord Al Masih Isa, you being gathered together, and my spirit, with the power of our Lord Al Masih Isa,\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "5", "sid": "1CO 5:5"}, "are to deliver such a one to Iblis for the destruction of the flesh, that the spirit may be saved in the day of the Lord\nIsa. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "6", "sid": "1CO 5:6"}, "Your boasting is not good. Don\u2019t you know that a little yeast leavens the whole lump?\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "7", "sid": "1CO 5:7"}, "Purge out the old yeast, that you may be a new lump, even as you are unleavened. For indeed Masih, our Passover, has been\nsacrificed in our place. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "8", "sid": "1CO 5:8"}, "Therefore let\u2019s keep the feast, not with old yeast, neither with the yeast of malice and wickedness, but with the\nunleavened bread of sincerity and truth. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "9", "sid": "1CO 5:9"}, "I wrote to you in my letter to have no company with sexual sinners;\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "10", "sid": "1CO 5:10"}, "yet not at all meaning with the sexual sinners of this world, or with the covetous and extortionists, or with idolaters;\nfor then you would have to leave the world. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "11", "sid": "1CO 5:11"}, "But as it is, I wrote to you not to associate with anyone who is called a brother who is a sexual sinner, or covetous, or\nan idolater, or a slanderer, or a drunkard, or an extortionist. Don\u2019t even eat with such a person.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "12", "sid": "1CO 5:12"}, "For what do I have to do with also judging those who are outside? Don\u2019t you judge those who are within?\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "13", "sid": "1CO 5:13"}, "But those who are outside, Allah judges. \u201cPut away the wicked man from amongst\nyourselves.\u201d", {"type": "note", "marker": "x", "content": [{"type": "char", "marker": "xo", "content": ["5:13 "]}, {"type": "char", "marker": "xt", "content": ["Deuteronomy 17:7; 19:19; 21:21; 22:21;\n24:7"]}], "caller": "+"}, " \n"]}, {"type": "chapter", "marker": "c", "number": "6", "sid": "1CO 6"}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "1", "sid": "1CO 6:1"}, "Dare any of you, having a matter against his neighbour, go to law before the unrighteous, and not before the saints?\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "2", "sid": "1CO 6:2"}, "Don\u2019t you know that the saints will judge the world? And if the world is judged by you, are you unworthy to judge the\nsmallest matters? \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "3", "sid": "1CO 6:3"}, "Don\u2019t you know that we will judge angels? How much more, things that pertain to this life?\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "4", "sid": "1CO 6:4"}, "If then you have to judge things pertaining to this life, do you set them to judge who are of no account in the assembly?\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "5", "sid": "1CO 6:5"}, "I say this to move you to shame. Isn\u2019t there even one wise man amongst you who would be able to decide between his\nbrothers? \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "6", "sid": "1CO 6:6"}, "But brother goes to law with brother, and that before unbelievers!\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "7", "sid": "1CO 6:7"}, "Therefore it is already altogether a defect in you, that you have lawsuits one with another. Why not rather be wronged?\nWhy not rather be defrauded? \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "8", "sid": "1CO 6:8"}, "No, but you yourselves do wrong and defraud, and that against your brothers.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "9", "sid": "1CO 6:9"}, "Or don\u2019t you know that the unrighteous will not inherit Allah\u2019s Kingdom? Don\u2019t be deceived. Neither the sexually immoral,\nnor idolaters, nor adulterers, nor male prostitutes, nor homosexuals,\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "10", "sid": "1CO 6:10"}, "nor thieves, nor covetous, nor drunkards, nor slanderers, nor extortionists, will inherit Allah\u2019s Kingdom.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "11", "sid": "1CO 6:11"}, "Some of you were such, but you were washed. But you were sanctified. But you were justified in the name of the Lord Isa,\nand in the Spirit of our Allah. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "12", "sid": "1CO 6:12"}, "\u201cAll things are lawful for me,\u201d but not all things are expedient. \u201cAll things are lawful for me,\u201d but I will not be\nbrought under the power of anything. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "13", "sid": "1CO 6:13"}, "\u201cFoods for the belly, and the belly for foods,\u201d but Allah will bring to nothing both it and them. But the body is not for\nsexual immorality, but for the Lord; and the Lord for the body. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "14", "sid": "1CO 6:14"}, "Now Allah raised up the Lord, and will also raise us up by his power.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "15", "sid": "1CO 6:15"}, "Don\u2019t you know that your bodies are members of Masih? Shall I then take the members of Masih and make them members of a\nprostitute? May it never be! \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "16", "sid": "1CO 6:16"}, "Or don\u2019t you know that he who is joined to a prostitute is one body? For, \u201cThe two\u201d, he says, \u201cwill become one\nflesh.\u201d", {"type": "note", "marker": "x", "content": [{"type": "char", "marker": "xo", "content": ["6:16 "]}, {"type": "char", "marker": "xt", "content": ["Genesis 2:24"]}], "caller": "+"}, " \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "17", "sid": "1CO 6:17"}, "But he who is joined to the Lord is one spirit. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "18", "sid": "1CO 6:18"}, "Flee sexual immorality! \u201cEvery sin that a man does is outside the body,\u201d but he who commits sexual immorality sins\nagainst his own body. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "19", "sid": "1CO 6:19"}, "Or don\u2019t you know that your body is a temple of the Holy Spirit who is in you, whom you have from Allah? You are not your\nown, \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "20", "sid": "1CO 6:20"}, "for you were bought with a price. Therefore glorify Allah in your body and in your spirit, which are Allah\u2019s.\n"]}, {"type": "chapter", "marker": "c", "number": "7", "sid": "1CO 7"}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "1", "sid": "1CO 7:1"}, "Now concerning the things about which you wrote to me: it is good for a man not to touch a woman.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "2", "sid": "1CO 7:2"}, "But, because of sexual immoralities, let each man have his own wife, and let each woman have her own husband.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "3", "sid": "1CO 7:3"}, "Let the husband give his wife the affection owed her,", {"type": "note", "marker": "f", "content": ["  ", {"type": "char", "marker": "fr", "content": ["7:3\n"]}, {"type": "char", "marker": "ft", "content": ["NU and TR have \u201cwhat is owed her\u201d instead of \u201cthe affection owed\nher\u201d."]}], "caller": "+"}, " and likewise also the wife her husband. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "4", "sid": "1CO 7:4"}, "The wife doesn\u2019t have authority over her own body, but the husband. Likewise also the husband doesn\u2019t have authority over\nhis own body, but the wife. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "5", "sid": "1CO 7:5"}, "Don\u2019t deprive one another, unless it is by consent for a season, that you may give yourselves to fasting and prayer, and\nmay be together again, that Iblis doesn\u2019t tempt you because of your lack of self-control.\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "6", "sid": "1CO 7:6"}, "But this I say by way of concession, not of commandment. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "7", "sid": "1CO 7:7"}, "Yet I wish that all men were like me. However each man has his own gift from Allah, one of this kind, and another of that\nkind. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "8", "sid": "1CO 7:8"}, "But I say to the unmarried and to widows, it is good for them if they remain even as I am.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "9", "sid": "1CO 7:9"}, "But if they don\u2019t have self-control, let them marry. For it\u2019s better to marry than to burn.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "10", "sid": "1CO 7:10"}, "But to the married I command\u2014not I, but the Lord\u2014that the wife not leave her husband\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "11", "sid": "1CO 7:11"}, "(but if she departs, let her remain unmarried, or else be reconciled to her husband), and that the husband not leave his\nwife. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "12", "sid": "1CO 7:12"}, "But to the rest I\u2014not the Lord\u2014say, if any brother has an unbelieving wife, and she is content to live with him, let him\nnot leave her. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "13", "sid": "1CO 7:13"}, "The woman who has an unbelieving husband, and he is content to live with her, let her not leave her husband.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "14", "sid": "1CO 7:14"}, "For the unbelieving husband is sanctified in the wife, and the unbelieving wife is sanctified in the husband. Otherwise\nyour children would be unclean, but now they are holy. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "15", "sid": "1CO 7:15"}, "Yet if the unbeliever departs, let there be separation. The brother or the sister is not under bondage in such cases, but\nAllah has called us in peace. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "16", "sid": "1CO 7:16"}, "For how do you know, wife, whether you will save your husband? Or how do you know, husband, whether you will save your\nwife? \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "17", "sid": "1CO 7:17"}, "Only, as the Lord has distributed to each man, as Allah has called each, so let him walk. So I command in all the\nassemblies. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "18", "sid": "1CO 7:18"}, "Was anyone called having been circumcised? Let him not become uncircumcised. Has anyone been called in uncircumcision?\nLet him not be circumcised. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "19", "sid": "1CO 7:19"}, "Circumcision is nothing, and uncircumcision is nothing, but the keeping of the commandments of Allah.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "20", "sid": "1CO 7:20"}, "Let each man stay in that calling in which he was called. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "21", "sid": "1CO 7:21"}, "Were you called being a bondservant? Don\u2019t let that bother you, but if you get an opportunity to become free, use it.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "22", "sid": "1CO 7:22"}, "For he who was called in the Lord being a bondservant is the Lord\u2019s free man. Likewise he who was called being free is\nMasih\u2019s bondservant. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "23", "sid": "1CO 7:23"}, "You were bought with a price. Don\u2019t become bondservants of men.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "24", "sid": "1CO 7:24"}, "Brothers, let each man, in whatever condition he was called, stay in that condition with Allah.\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "25", "sid": "1CO 7:25"}, "Now concerning virgins, I have no commandment from the Lord, but I give my judgement as one who has obtained mercy from\nthe Lord to be trustworthy. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "26", "sid": "1CO 7:26"}, "Therefore I think that because of the distress that is on us, that it\u2019s good for a man to remain as he is.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "27", "sid": "1CO 7:27"}, "Are you bound to a wife? Don\u2019t seek to be freed. Are you free from a wife? Don\u2019t seek a wife.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "28", "sid": "1CO 7:28"}, "But if you marry, you have not sinned. If a virgin marries, she has not sinned. Yet such will have oppression in the\nflesh, and I want to spare you. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "29", "sid": "1CO 7:29"}, "But I say this, brothers: the time is short, that from now on, both those who have wives may be as though they had none;\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "30", "sid": "1CO 7:30"}, "and those who weep, as though they didn\u2019t weep; and those who rejoice, as though they didn\u2019t rejoice; and those who buy,\nas though they didn\u2019t possess; \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "31", "sid": "1CO 7:31"}, "and those who use the world, as not using it to the fullest. For the mode of this world passes away.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "32", "sid": "1CO 7:32"}, "But I desire to have you to be free from cares. He who is unmarried is concerned for the things of the Lord, how he may\nplease the Lord; \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "33", "sid": "1CO 7:33"}, "but he who is married is concerned about the things of the world, how he may please his wife.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "34", "sid": "1CO 7:34"}, "There is also a difference between a wife and a virgin. The unmarried woman cares about the things of the Lord, that she\nmay be holy both in body and in spirit. But she who is married cares about the things of the world\u2014how she may please her\nhusband. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "35", "sid": "1CO 7:35"}, "This I say for your own profit; not that I may ensnare you, but for that which is appropriate, and that you may attend to\nthe Lord without distraction. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "36", "sid": "1CO 7:36"}, "But if any man thinks that he is behaving inappropriately towards his virgin, if she is past the flower of her age, and\nif need so requires, let him do what he desires. He doesn\u2019t sin. Let them marry.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "37", "sid": "1CO 7:37"}, "But he who stands steadfast in his heart, having no urgency, but has power over his own will, and has determined in his\nown heart to keep his own virgin, does well. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "38", "sid": "1CO 7:38"}, "So then both he who gives his own virgin in marriage does well, and he who doesn\u2019t give her in marriage does better.\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "39", "sid": "1CO 7:39"}, "A wife is bound by law for as long as her husband lives; but if the husband is dead, she is free to be married to\nwhomever she desires, only in the Lord. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "40", "sid": "1CO 7:40"}, "But she is happier if she stays as she is, in my judgement, and I think that I also have Allah\u2019s Spirit.\n"]}, {"type": "chapter", "marker": "c", "number": "8", "sid": "1CO 8"}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "1", "sid": "1CO 8:1"}, "Now concerning things sacrificed to idols: We know that we all have knowledge. Knowledge puffs up, but love builds up.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "2", "sid": "1CO 8:2"}, "But if anyone thinks that he knows anything, he doesn\u2019t yet know as he ought to know.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "3", "sid": "1CO 8:3"}, "But if anyone loves Allah, the same is known by him. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "4", "sid": "1CO 8:4"}, "Therefore concerning the eating of things sacrificed to idols, we know that no idol is anything in the world, and that\nthere is no other Allah but one. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "5", "sid": "1CO 8:5"}, "For though there are things that are called \u201cgods\u201d, whether in the heavens or on earth; as there are many \u201cgods\u201d and many\n\u201clords\u201d; \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "6", "sid": "1CO 8:6"}, "yet to us there is one Allah, the Father, of whom are all things, and we for him; and one Lord, Al Masih Isa, through whom\nare all things, and we live through him. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "7", "sid": "1CO 8:7"}, "However, that knowledge isn\u2019t in all men. But some, with consciousness of the idol until now, eat as of a thing sacrificed\nto an idol, and their conscience, being weak, is defiled. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "8", "sid": "1CO 8:8"}, "But food will not commend us to Allah. For neither, if we don\u2019t eat, are we the worse; nor, if we eat, are we the better.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "9", "sid": "1CO 8:9"}, "But be careful that by no means does this liberty of yours become a stumbling block to the weak.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "10", "sid": "1CO 8:10"}, "For if a man sees you who have knowledge sitting in an idol\u2019s temple, won\u2019t his conscience, if he is weak, be emboldened\nto eat things sacrificed to idols? \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "11", "sid": "1CO 8:11"}, "And through your knowledge, he who is weak perishes, the brother for whose sake Masih died.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "12", "sid": "1CO 8:12"}, "Thus, sinning against the brothers, and wounding their conscience when it is weak, you sin against Masih.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "13", "sid": "1CO 8:13"}, "Therefore if food causes my brother to stumble, I will eat no meat forever more, that I don\u2019t cause my brother to\nstumble. \n"]}, {"type": "chapter", "marker": "c", "number": "9", "sid": "1CO 9"}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "1", "sid": "1CO 9:1"}, "Am I not free? Am I not an apostle? Haven\u2019t I seen Al Masih Isa, our Lord? Aren\u2019t you my work in the Lord?\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "2", "sid": "1CO 9:2"}, "If to others I am not an apostle, yet at least I am to you; for you are the seal of my apostleship in the Lord.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "3", "sid": "1CO 9:3"}, "My defence to those who examine me is this: \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "4", "sid": "1CO 9:4"}, "Have we no right to eat and to drink? \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "5", "sid": "1CO 9:5"}, "Have we no right to take along a wife who is a believer, even as the rest of the apostles, and the brothers of the Lord,\nand Cephas? \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "6", "sid": "1CO 9:6"}, "Or have only Barnabas and I no right to not work? \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "7", "sid": "1CO 9:7"}, "What soldier ever serves at his own expense? Who plants a vineyard, and doesn\u2019t eat of its fruit? Or who feeds a flock,\nand doesn\u2019t drink from the flock\u2019s milk? \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "8", "sid": "1CO 9:8"}, "Do I speak these things according to the ways of men? Or doesn\u2019t the law also say the same thing?\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "9", "sid": "1CO 9:9"}, "For it is written in the law of Musa, \u201cYou shall not muzzle an ox while it treads out the\ngrain.\u201d", {"type": "note", "marker": "x", "content": [{"type": "char", "marker": "xo", "content": ["9:9 "]}, {"type": "char", "marker": "xt", "content": ["Deuteronomy 25:4"]}], "caller": "+"}, " Is it for the oxen that Allah cares,\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "10", "sid": "1CO 9:10"}, "or does he say it assuredly for our sake? Yes, it was written for our sake, because he who ploughs ought to plough in\nhope, and he who threshes in hope should partake of his hope. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "11", "sid": "1CO 9:11"}, "If we sowed to you spiritual things, is it a great thing if we reap your fleshly things?\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "12", "sid": "1CO 9:12"}, "If others partake of this right over you, don\u2019t we yet more? Nevertheless we didn\u2019t use this right, but we bear all\nthings, that we may cause no hindrance to the Good News of Masih.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "13", "sid": "1CO 9:13"}, "Don\u2019t you know that those who serve around sacred things eat from the things of the temple, and those who wait on the\naltar have their portion with the altar? \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "14", "sid": "1CO 9:14"}, "Even so the Lord ordained that those who proclaim the Good News should live from the Good News.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "15", "sid": "1CO 9:15"}, "But I have used none of these things, and I don\u2019t write these things that it may be done so in my case; for I would\nrather die, than that anyone should make my boasting void. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "16", "sid": "1CO 9:16"}, "For if I preach the Good News, I have nothing to boast about; for necessity is laid on me; but woe is to me if I don\u2019t\npreach the Good News. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "17", "sid": "1CO 9:17"}, "For if I do this of my own will, I have a reward. But if not of my own will, I have a stewardship entrusted to me.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "18", "sid": "1CO 9:18"}, "What then is my reward? That when I preach the Good News, I may present the Good News of Masih without charge, so as not\nto abuse my authority in the Good News. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "19", "sid": "1CO 9:19"}, "For though I was free from all, I brought myself under bondage to all, that I might gain the more.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "20", "sid": "1CO 9:20"}, "To the Jews I became as a Jew, that I might gain Jews; to those who are under the law, as under the law, that I might\ngain those who are under the law; \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "21", "sid": "1CO 9:21"}, "to those who are without law, as without law (not being without law towards Allah, but under law towards Masih), that I\nmight win those who are without law. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "22", "sid": "1CO 9:22"}, "To the weak I became as weak, that I might gain the weak. I have become all things to all men, that I may by all means\nsave some. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "23", "sid": "1CO 9:23"}, "Now I do this for the sake of the Good News, that I may be a joint partaker of it.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "24", "sid": "1CO 9:24"}, "Don\u2019t you know that those who run in a race all run, but one receives the prize? Run like that, that you may win.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "25", "sid": "1CO 9:25"}, "Every man who strives in the games exercises self-control in all things. Now they do it to receive a corruptible crown,\nbut we an incorruptible. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "26", "sid": "1CO 9:26"}, "I therefore run like that, not aimlessly. I fight like that, not beating the air,\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "27", "sid": "1CO 9:27"}, "but I beat my body and bring it into submission, lest by any means, after I have preached to others, I myself should be\nrejected. \n"]}, {"type": "chapter", "marker": "c", "number": "10", "sid": "1CO 10"}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "1", "sid": "1CO 10:1"}, "Now I would not have you ignorant, brothers, that our fathers were all under the cloud, and all passed through the sea;\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "2", "sid": "1CO 10:2"}, "and were all baptised into Musa in the cloud and in the sea;\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "3", "sid": "1CO 10:3"}, "and all ate the same spiritual food; \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "4", "sid": "1CO 10:4"}, "and all drank the same spiritual drink. For they drank of a spiritual rock that followed them, and the rock was Masih.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "5", "sid": "1CO 10:5"}, "However with most of them, Allah was not well pleased, for they were overthrown in the wilderness.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "6", "sid": "1CO 10:6"}, "Now these things were our examples, to the intent we should not lust after evil things, as they also lusted.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "7", "sid": "1CO 10:7"}, "Don\u2019t be idolaters, as some of them were. As it is written, \u201cThe people sat down to eat and drink, and rose up to\nplay.\u201d", {"type": "note", "marker": "x", "content": [{"type": "char", "marker": "xo", "content": ["10:7 "]}, {"type": "char", "marker": "xt", "content": ["Exodus 32:6"]}], "caller": "+"}, " \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "8", "sid": "1CO 10:8"}, "Let\u2019s not commit sexual immorality, as some of them committed, and in one day twenty-three thousand fell.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "9", "sid": "1CO 10:9"}, "Let\u2019s not test Masih,", {"type": "note", "marker": "f", "content": ["  ", {"type": "char", "marker": "fr", "content": ["10:9 "]}, {"type": "char", "marker": "ft", "content": ["NU reads \u201cthe Lord\u201d instead of\n\u201cMasih\u201d."]}], "caller": "+"}, " as some of them tested, and perished by the serpents.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "10", "sid": "1CO 10:10"}, "Don\u2019t grumble, as some of them also grumbled, and perished by the destroyer.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "11", "sid": "1CO 10:11"}, "Now all these things happened to them by way of example, and they were written for our admonition, on whom the ends of\nthe ages have come. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "12", "sid": "1CO 10:12"}, "Therefore let him who thinks he stands be careful that he doesn\u2019t fall.\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "13", "sid": "1CO 10:13"}, "No temptation has taken you except what is common to man. Allah is faithful, who will not allow you to be tempted above\nwhat you are able, but will with the temptation also make the way of escape, that you may be able to endure it.\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "14", "sid": "1CO 10:14"}, "Therefore, my beloved, flee from idolatry. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "15", "sid": "1CO 10:15"}, "I speak as to wise men. Judge what I say. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "16", "sid": "1CO 10:16"}, "The cup of blessing which we bless, isn\u2019t it a sharing of the blood of Masih? The bread which we break, isn\u2019t it a\nsharing of the body of Masih? \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "17", "sid": "1CO 10:17"}, "Because there is one loaf of bread, we, who are many, are one body; for we all partake of the one loaf of bread.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "18", "sid": "1CO 10:18"}, "Consider Israel according to the flesh. Don\u2019t those who eat the sacrifices participate in the altar?\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "19", "sid": "1CO 10:19"}, "What am I saying then? That a thing sacrificed to idols is anything, or that an idol is anything?\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "20", "sid": "1CO 10:20"}, "But I say that the things which the Gentiles sacrifice, they sacrifice to demons, and not to Allah, and I don\u2019t desire\nthat you would have fellowship with demons. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "21", "sid": "1CO 10:21"}, "You can\u2019t both drink the cup of the Lord and the cup of demons. You can\u2019t both partake of the table of the Lord and of\nthe table of demons. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "22", "sid": "1CO 10:22"}, "Or do we provoke the Lord to jealousy? Are we stronger than he?\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "23", "sid": "1CO 10:23"}, "\u201cAll things are lawful for me,\u201d but not all things are profitable. \u201cAll things are lawful for me,\u201d but not all things\nbuild up. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "24", "sid": "1CO 10:24"}, "Let no one seek his own, but each one his neighbour\u2019s good.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "25", "sid": "1CO 10:25"}, "Whatever is sold in the butcher shop, eat, asking no question for the sake of conscience,\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "26", "sid": "1CO 10:26"}, "for \u201cthe earth is the Lord\u2019s, and its fullness.\u201d", {"type": "note", "marker": "x", "content": [{"type": "char", "marker": "xo", "content": ["10:26\n"]}, {"type": "char", "marker": "xt", "content": ["Zabur 24:1 "]}], "caller": "+"}, " \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "27", "sid": "1CO 10:27"}, "But if one of those who don\u2019t believe invites you to a meal, and you are inclined to go, eat whatever is set before you,\nasking no questions for the sake of conscience. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "28", "sid": "1CO 10:28"}, "But if anyone says to you, \u201cThis was offered to idols,\u201d don\u2019t eat it for the sake of the one who told you, and for the\nsake of conscience. For \u201cthe earth is the Lord\u2019s, with all its fullness.\u201d\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "29", "sid": "1CO 10:29"}, "Conscience, I say, not your own, but the other\u2019s conscience. For why is my liberty judged by another conscience?\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "30", "sid": "1CO 10:30"}, "If I partake with thankfulness, why am I denounced for something I give thanks for?\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "31", "sid": "1CO 10:31"}, "Whether therefore you eat, or drink, or whatever you do, do all to the glory of Allah.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "32", "sid": "1CO 10:32"}, "Give no occasion for stumbling, whether to Jews, or to Greeks, or to the assembly of Allah;\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "33", "sid": "1CO 10:33"}, "even as I also please all men in all things, not seeking my own profit, but the profit of the many, that they may be\nsaved. \n"]}, {"type": "chapter", "marker": "c", "number": "11", "sid": "1CO 11"}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "1", "sid": "1CO 11:1"}, "Be imitators of me, even as I also am of Masih. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "2", "sid": "1CO 11:2"}, "Now I praise you, brothers, that you remember me in all things, and hold firm the traditions, even as I delivered them to\nyou. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "3", "sid": "1CO 11:3"}, "But I would have you know that the head", {"type": "note", "marker": "f", "content": ["  ", {"type": "char", "marker": "fr", "content": ["11:3 "]}, {"type": "char", "marker": "ft", "content": ["or,\norigin"]}], "caller": "+"}, " of every man is Masih, and the head", {"type": "note", "marker": "f", "content": ["  ", {"type": "char", "marker": "fr", "content": ["11:3 "]}, {"type": "char", "marker": "ft", "content": ["or,\norigin"]}], "caller": "+"}, " of the woman is man, and the head", {"type": "note", "marker": "f", "content": ["  ", {"type": "char", "marker": "fr", "content": ["11:3 "]}, {"type": "char", "marker": "ft", "content": ["or,\norigin"]}], "caller": "+"}, " of Masih is Allah. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "4", "sid": "1CO 11:4"}, "Every man praying or prophesying, having his head covered, dishonours his head.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "5", "sid": "1CO 11:5"}, "But every woman praying or prophesying with her head uncovered dishonours her head. For it is one and the same thing as if\nshe were shaved. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "6", "sid": "1CO 11:6"}, "For if a woman is not covered, let her hair also be cut off. But if it is shameful for a woman to have her hair cut off or\nbe shaved, let her be covered. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "7", "sid": "1CO 11:7"}, "For a man indeed ought not to have his head covered, because he is the image and glory of Allah, but the woman is the\nglory of the man. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "8", "sid": "1CO 11:8"}, "For man is not from woman, but woman from man; \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "9", "sid": "1CO 11:9"}, "for man wasn\u2019t created for the woman, but woman for the man.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "10", "sid": "1CO 11:10"}, "For this cause the woman ought to have authority over her own head, because of the angels.\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "11", "sid": "1CO 11:11"}, "Nevertheless, neither is the woman independent of the man, nor the man independent of the woman, in the Lord.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "12", "sid": "1CO 11:12"}, "For as woman came from man, so a man also comes through a woman; but all things are from Allah.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "13", "sid": "1CO 11:13"}, "Judge for yourselves. Is it appropriate that a woman pray to Allah unveiled?\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "14", "sid": "1CO 11:14"}, "Doesn\u2019t even nature itself teach you that if a man has long hair, it is a dishonour to him?\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "15", "sid": "1CO 11:15"}, "But if a woman has long hair, it is a glory to her, for her hair is given to her for a covering.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "16", "sid": "1CO 11:16"}, "But if any man seems to be contentious, we have no such custom, neither do Allah\u2019s assemblies.\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "17", "sid": "1CO 11:17"}, "But in giving you this command, I don\u2019t praise you, that you come together not for the better but for the worse.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "18", "sid": "1CO 11:18"}, "For first of all, when you come together in the assembly, I hear that divisions exist amongst you, and I partly believe\nit. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "19", "sid": "1CO 11:19"}, "For there also must be factions amongst you, that those who are approved may be revealed amongst you.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "20", "sid": "1CO 11:20"}, "When therefore you assemble yourselves together, it is not the Lord\u2019s supper that you eat.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "21", "sid": "1CO 11:21"}, "For in your eating each one takes his own supper first. One is hungry, and another is drunken.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "22", "sid": "1CO 11:22"}, "What, don\u2019t you have houses to eat and to drink in? Or do you despise Allah\u2019s assembly and put them to shame who don\u2019t\nhave enough? What shall I tell you? Shall I praise you? In this I don\u2019t praise you.\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "23", "sid": "1CO 11:23"}, "For I received from the Lord that which also I delivered to you, that the Lord Isa on the night in which he was betrayed\ntook bread. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "24", "sid": "1CO 11:24"}, "When he had given thanks, he broke it and said, ", {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["\u201cTake, eat. This is my body, which is broken for you. Do this in\nmemory of me.\u201d"]}, " \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "25", "sid": "1CO 11:25"}, "In the same way he also took the cup, after supper, saying,\n", {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["\u201cThis cup is the new covenant in my blood. Do this, as often as you drink, in memory of\nme.\u201d"]}, " \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "26", "sid": "1CO 11:26"}, "For as often as you eat this bread and drink this cup, you proclaim the Lord\u2019s death until he comes.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "27", "sid": "1CO 11:27"}, "Therefore whoever eats this bread or drinks the Lord\u2019s cup in a way unworthy of the Lord will be guilty of the body and\nthe blood of the Lord. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "28", "sid": "1CO 11:28"}, "But let a man examine himself, and so let him eat of the bread, and drink of the cup.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "29", "sid": "1CO 11:29"}, "For he who eats and drinks in an unworthy way eats and drinks judgement to himself if he doesn\u2019t discern the Lord\u2019s body.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "30", "sid": "1CO 11:30"}, "For this cause many amongst you are weak and sickly, and not a few sleep.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "31", "sid": "1CO 11:31"}, "For if we discerned ourselves, we wouldn\u2019t be judged. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "32", "sid": "1CO 11:32"}, "But when we are judged, we are punished by the Lord, that we may not be condemned with the world.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "33", "sid": "1CO 11:33"}, "Therefore, my brothers, when you come together to eat, wait for one another.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "34", "sid": "1CO 11:34"}, "But if anyone is hungry, let him eat at home, lest your coming together be for judgement. The rest I will set in order\nwhenever I come. \n"]}, {"type": "chapter", "marker": "c", "number": "12", "sid": "1CO 12"}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "1", "sid": "1CO 12:1"}, "Now concerning spiritual things, brothers, I don\u2019t want you to be ignorant.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "2", "sid": "1CO 12:2"}, "You know that when you were heathen,", {"type": "note", "marker": "f", "content": ["  ", {"type": "char", "marker": "fr", "content": ["12:2 "]}, {"type": "char", "marker": "ft", "content": ["or Gentiles"]}], "caller": "+"}, " you were led away to those mute idols, however you\nmight be led. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "3", "sid": "1CO 12:3"}, "Therefore I make known to you that no man speaking by Allah\u2019s Spirit says, \u201cIsa is accursed.\u201d No one can say, \u201cIsa is\nLord,\u201d but by the Holy Spirit. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "4", "sid": "1CO 12:4"}, "Now there are various kinds of gifts, but the same Spirit. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "5", "sid": "1CO 12:5"}, "There are various kinds of service, and the same Lord. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "6", "sid": "1CO 12:6"}, "There are various kinds of workings, but the same Allah, who works all things in all.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "7", "sid": "1CO 12:7"}, "But to each one is given the manifestation of the Spirit for the profit of all.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "8", "sid": "1CO 12:8"}, "For to one is given through the Spirit the word of wisdom, and to another the word of knowledge, according to the same\nSpirit; \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "9", "sid": "1CO 12:9"}, "to another faith, by the same Spirit; and to another gifts of healings, by the same Spirit;\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "10", "sid": "1CO 12:10"}, "and to another workings of miracles; and to another prophecy; and to another discerning of spirits; to another different\nkinds of languages; and to another the interpretation of languages.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "11", "sid": "1CO 12:11"}, "But the one and the same Spirit produces all of these, distributing to each one separately as he desires.\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "12", "sid": "1CO 12:12"}, "For as the body is one, and has many members, and all the members of the body, being many, are one body; so also is\nMasih. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "13", "sid": "1CO 12:13"}, "For in one Spirit we were all baptised into one body, whether Jews or Greeks, whether bond or free; and were all given to\ndrink into one Spirit. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "14", "sid": "1CO 12:14"}, "For the body is not one member, but many. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "15", "sid": "1CO 12:15"}, "If the foot would say, \u201cBecause I\u2019m not the hand, I\u2019m not part of the body,\u201d it is not therefore not part of the body.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "16", "sid": "1CO 12:16"}, "If the ear would say, \u201cBecause I\u2019m not the eye, I\u2019m not part of the body,\u201d it\u2019s not therefore not part of the body.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "17", "sid": "1CO 12:17"}, "If the whole body were an eye, where would the hearing be? If the whole were hearing, where would the smelling be?\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "18", "sid": "1CO 12:18"}, "But now Allah has set the members, each one of them, in the body, just as he desired.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "19", "sid": "1CO 12:19"}, "If they were all one member, where would the body be? \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "20", "sid": "1CO 12:20"}, "But now they are many members, but one body. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "21", "sid": "1CO 12:21"}, "The eye can\u2019t tell the hand, \u201cI have no need for you,\u201d or again the head to the feet, \u201cI have no need for you.\u201d\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "22", "sid": "1CO 12:22"}, "No, much rather, those members of the body which seem to be weaker are necessary.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "23", "sid": "1CO 12:23"}, "Those parts of the body which we think to be less honourable, on those we bestow more abundant honour; and our\nunpresentable parts have more abundant propriety; \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "24", "sid": "1CO 12:24"}, "whereas our presentable parts have no such need. But Allah composed the body together, giving more abundant honour to the\ninferior part, \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "25", "sid": "1CO 12:25"}, "that there should be no division in the body, but that the members should have the same care for one another.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "26", "sid": "1CO 12:26"}, "When one member suffers, all the members suffer with it. When one member is honoured, all the members rejoice with it.\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "27", "sid": "1CO 12:27"}, "Now you are the body of Masih, and members individually. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "28", "sid": "1CO 12:28"}, "Allah has set some in the assembly: first apostles, second prophets, third teachers, then miracle workers, then gifts of\nhealings, helps, governments, and various kinds of languages. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "29", "sid": "1CO 12:29"}, "Are all apostles? Are all prophets? Are all teachers? Are all miracle workers?\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "30", "sid": "1CO 12:30"}, "Do all have gifts of healings? Do all speak with various languages? Do all interpret?\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "31", "sid": "1CO 12:31"}, "But earnestly desire the best gifts. Moreover, I show a most excellent way to you.\n"]}, {"type": "chapter", "marker": "c", "number": "13", "sid": "1CO 13"}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "1", "sid": "1CO 13:1"}, "If I speak with the languages of men and of angels, but don\u2019t have love, I have become sounding brass, or a clanging\ncymbal. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "2", "sid": "1CO 13:2"}, "If I have the gift of prophecy, and know all mysteries and all knowledge; and if I have all faith, so as to remove\nmountains, but don\u2019t have love, I am nothing. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "3", "sid": "1CO 13:3"}, "If I give away all my goods to feed the poor, and if I give my body to be burnt, but don\u2019t have love, it profits me\nnothing. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "4", "sid": "1CO 13:4"}, "Love is patient and is kind. Love doesn\u2019t envy. Love doesn\u2019t brag, is not proud,\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "5", "sid": "1CO 13:5"}, "doesn\u2019t behave itself inappropriately, doesn\u2019t seek its own way, is not provoked, takes no account of evil;\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "6", "sid": "1CO 13:6"}, "doesn\u2019t rejoice in unrighteousness, but rejoices with the truth;\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "7", "sid": "1CO 13:7"}, "bears all things, believes all things, hopes all things, and endures all things.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "8", "sid": "1CO 13:8"}, "Love never fails. But where there are prophecies, they will be done away with. Where there are various languages, they\nwill cease. Where there is knowledge, it will be done away with.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "9", "sid": "1CO 13:9"}, "For we know in part and we prophesy in part; \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "10", "sid": "1CO 13:10"}, "but when that which is complete has come, then that which is partial will be done away with.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "11", "sid": "1CO 13:11"}, "When I was a child, I spoke as a child, I felt as a child, I thought as a child. Now that I have become a man, I have put\naway childish things. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "12", "sid": "1CO 13:12"}, "For now we see in a mirror, dimly, but then face to face. Now I know in part, but then I will know fully, even as I was\nalso fully known. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "13", "sid": "1CO 13:13"}, "But now faith, hope, and love remain\u2014these three. The greatest of these is love.\n"]}, {"type": "chapter", "marker": "c", "number": "14", "sid": "1CO 14"}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "1", "sid": "1CO 14:1"}, "Follow after love and earnestly desire spiritual gifts, but especially that you may prophesy.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "2", "sid": "1CO 14:2"}, "For he who speaks in another language speaks not to men, but to Allah; for no one understands; but in the Spirit he speaks\nmysteries. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "3", "sid": "1CO 14:3"}, "But he who prophesies speaks to men for their edification, exhortation, and consolation.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "4", "sid": "1CO 14:4"}, "He who speaks in another language edifies himself, but he who prophesies edifies the assembly.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "5", "sid": "1CO 14:5"}, "Now I desire to have you all speak with other languages, but rather that you would prophesy. For he is greater who\nprophesies than he who speaks with other languages, unless he interprets, that the assembly may be built up.\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "6", "sid": "1CO 14:6"}, "But now, brothers,", {"type": "note", "marker": "f", "content": ["  ", {"type": "char", "marker": "fr", "content": ["14:6 "]}, {"type": "char", "marker": "ft", "content": ["The word for \u201cbrothers\u201d here and where context allows may also be correctly\ntranslated \u201cbrothers and sisters\u201d or \u201csiblings.\u201d "]}], "caller": "+"}, " if I come to you speaking with other languages, what would I profit you,\nunless I speak to you either by way of revelation, or of knowledge, or of prophesying, or of teaching?\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "7", "sid": "1CO 14:7"}, "Even things without life, giving a voice, whether pipe or harp, if they didn\u2019t give a distinction in the sounds, how would\nit be known what is piped or harped? \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "8", "sid": "1CO 14:8"}, "For if the trumpet gave an uncertain sound, who would prepare himself for war?\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "9", "sid": "1CO 14:9"}, "So also you, unless you uttered by the tongue words easy to understand, how would it be known what is spoken? For you\nwould be speaking into the air. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "10", "sid": "1CO 14:10"}, "There are, it may be, so many kinds of sounds in the world, and none of them is without meaning.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "11", "sid": "1CO 14:11"}, "If then I don\u2019t know the meaning of the sound, I would be to him who speaks a foreigner, and he who speaks would be a\nforeigner to me. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "12", "sid": "1CO 14:12"}, "So also you, since you are zealous for spiritual gifts, seek that you may abound to the building up of the assembly.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "13", "sid": "1CO 14:13"}, "Therefore let him who speaks in another language pray that he may interpret.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "14", "sid": "1CO 14:14"}, "For if I pray in another language, my spirit prays, but my understanding is unfruitful.\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "15", "sid": "1CO 14:15"}, "What is it then? I will pray with the spirit, and I will pray with the understanding also. I will sing with the spirit,\nand I will sing with the understanding also. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "16", "sid": "1CO 14:16"}, "Otherwise if you bless with the spirit, how will he who fills the place of the unlearned say the \u201cAmen\u201d at your giving of\nthanks, seeing he doesn\u2019t know what you say? \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "17", "sid": "1CO 14:17"}, "For you most certainly give thanks well, but the other person is not built up.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "18", "sid": "1CO 14:18"}, "I thank my Allah, I speak with other languages more than you all.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "19", "sid": "1CO 14:19"}, "However in the assembly I would rather speak five words with my understanding, that I might instruct others also, than\nten thousand words in another language. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "20", "sid": "1CO 14:20"}, "Brothers, don\u2019t be children in thoughts, yet in malice be babies, but in thoughts be mature.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "21", "sid": "1CO 14:21"}, "In the law it is written, \u201cBy men of strange languages and by the lips of strangers I will speak to this people. They\nwon\u2019t even hear me that way, says the Lord.\u201d", {"type": "note", "marker": "x", "content": [{"type": "char", "marker": "xo", "content": ["14:21 "]}, {"type": "char", "marker": "xt", "content": ["Isaiah\n28:11-12"]}], "caller": "+"}, " \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "22", "sid": "1CO 14:22"}, "Therefore other languages are for a sign, not to those who believe, but to the unbelieving; but prophesying is for a\nsign, not to the unbelieving, but to those who believe. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "23", "sid": "1CO 14:23"}, "If therefore the whole assembly is assembled together and all speak with other languages, and unlearned or unbelieving\npeople come in, won\u2019t they say that you are crazy? \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "24", "sid": "1CO 14:24"}, "But if all prophesy, and someone unbelieving or unlearned comes in, he is reproved by all, and he is judged by all.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "25", "sid": "1CO 14:25"}, "And thus the secrets of his heart are revealed. So he will fall down on his face and worship Allah, declaring that Allah\nis amongst you indeed. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "26", "sid": "1CO 14:26"}, "What is it then, brothers? When you come together, each one of you has a psalm, has a teaching, has a revelation, has\nanother language, or has an interpretation. Let all things be done to build each other up.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "27", "sid": "1CO 14:27"}, "If any man speaks in another language, let it be two, or at the most three, and in turn; and let one interpret.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "28", "sid": "1CO 14:28"}, "But if there is no interpreter, let him keep silent in the assembly, and let him speak to himself, and to Allah.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "29", "sid": "1CO 14:29"}, "Let the prophets speak, two or three, and let the others discern.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "30", "sid": "1CO 14:30"}, "But if a revelation is made to another sitting by, let the first keep silent.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "31", "sid": "1CO 14:31"}, "For you all can prophesy one by one, that all may learn, and all may be exhorted.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "32", "sid": "1CO 14:32"}, "The spirits of the prophets are subject to the prophets, \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "33", "sid": "1CO 14:33"}, "for Allah is not Allah of confusion, but of peace, as in all the assemblies of the saints.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "34", "sid": "1CO 14:34"}, "Let the wives be quiet in the assemblies, for it has not been permitted for them to be talking except in submission, as\nthe law also says,", {"type": "note", "marker": "x", "content": [{"type": "char", "marker": "xo", "content": ["14:34 "]}, {"type": "char", "marker": "xt", "content": ["Deuteronomy 27:9"]}], "caller": "+"}, " \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "35", "sid": "1CO 14:35"}, "if they desire to learn anything. \u201cLet them ask their own husbands at home, for it is shameful for a wife to be talking\nin the assembly.\u201d \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "36", "sid": "1CO 14:36"}, "What!? Was it from you that the word of Allah went out? Or did it come to you alone?\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "37", "sid": "1CO 14:37"}, "If any man thinks himself to be a prophet, or spiritual, let him recognise the things which I write to you, that they are\nthe commandment of the Lord. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "38", "sid": "1CO 14:38"}, "But if anyone is ignorant, let him be ignorant. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "39", "sid": "1CO 14:39"}, "Therefore, brothers, desire earnestly to prophesy, and don\u2019t forbid speaking with other languages.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "40", "sid": "1CO 14:40"}, "Let all things be done decently and in order. \n"]}, {"type": "chapter", "marker": "c", "number": "15", "sid": "1CO 15"}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "1", "sid": "1CO 15:1"}, "Now I declare to you, brothers, the Good News which I preached to you, which also you received, in which you also stand,\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "2", "sid": "1CO 15:2"}, "by which also you are saved, if you hold firmly the word which I preached to you\u2014unless you believed in vain.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "3", "sid": "1CO 15:3"}, "For I delivered to you first of all that which I also received: that Masih died for our sins according to the Scriptures,\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "4", "sid": "1CO 15:4"}, "that he was buried, that he was raised on the third day according to the Scriptures,\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "5", "sid": "1CO 15:5"}, "and that he appeared to Cephas, then to the twelve. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "6", "sid": "1CO 15:6"}, "Then he appeared to over five hundred brothers at once, most of whom remain until now, but some have also fallen asleep.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "7", "sid": "1CO 15:7"}, "Then he appeared to Yaqub, then to all the apostles, \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "8", "sid": "1CO 15:8"}, "and last of all, as to the child born at the wrong time, he appeared to me also.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "9", "sid": "1CO 15:9"}, "For I am the least of the apostles, who is not worthy to be called an apostle, because I persecuted the assembly of Allah.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "10", "sid": "1CO 15:10"}, "But by the grace of Allah I am what I am. His grace which was given to me was not futile, but I worked more than all of\nthem; yet not I, but the grace of Allah which was with me. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "11", "sid": "1CO 15:11"}, "Whether then it is I or they, so we preach, and so you believed.\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "12", "sid": "1CO 15:12"}, "Now if Masih is preached, that he has been raised from the dead, how do some amongst you say that there is no\nresurrection of the dead? \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "13", "sid": "1CO 15:13"}, "But if there is no resurrection of the dead, neither has Masih been raised.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "14", "sid": "1CO 15:14"}, "If Masih has not been raised, then our preaching is in vain, and your faith also is in vain.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "15", "sid": "1CO 15:15"}, "Yes, we are also found false witnesses of Allah, because we testified about Allah that he raised up Masih, whom he didn\u2019t\nraise up, if it is so that the dead are not raised. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "16", "sid": "1CO 15:16"}, "For if the dead aren\u2019t raised, neither has Masih been raised.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "17", "sid": "1CO 15:17"}, "If Masih has not been raised, your faith is vain; you are still in your sins.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "18", "sid": "1CO 15:18"}, "Then they also who are fallen asleep in Masih have perished.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "19", "sid": "1CO 15:19"}, "If we have only hoped in Masih in this life, we are of all men most pitiable.\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "20", "sid": "1CO 15:20"}, "But now Masih has been raised from the dead. He became the first fruits of those who are asleep.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "21", "sid": "1CO 15:21"}, "For since death came by man, the resurrection of the dead also came by man.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "22", "sid": "1CO 15:22"}, "For as in Adam all die, so also in Masih all will be made alive.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "23", "sid": "1CO 15:23"}, "But each in his own order: Masih the first fruits, then those who are Masih\u2019s, at his coming.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "24", "sid": "1CO 15:24"}, "Then the end comes, when he will deliver up the Kingdom to Allah, even the Father, when he will have abolished all rule\nand all authority and power. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "25", "sid": "1CO 15:25"}, "For he must reign until he has put all his enemies under his feet.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "26", "sid": "1CO 15:26"}, "The last enemy that will be abolished is death. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "27", "sid": "1CO 15:27"}, "For, \u201cHe put all things in subjection under his feet.\u201d", {"type": "note", "marker": "x", "content": [{"type": "char", "marker": "xo", "content": ["15:27 "]}, {"type": "char", "marker": "xt", "content": ["Zabur 8:6"]}], "caller": "+"}, " But when he says, \u201cAll things are put in subjection\u201d, it is evident that he is excepted who\nsubjected all things to him. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "28", "sid": "1CO 15:28"}, "When all things have been subjected to him, then the Son will also himself be subjected to him who subjected all things\nto him, that Allah may be all in all. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "29", "sid": "1CO 15:29"}, "Or else what will they do who are baptised for the dead? If the dead aren\u2019t raised at all, why then are they baptised for\nthe dead? \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "30", "sid": "1CO 15:30"}, "Why do we also stand in jeopardy every hour? \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "31", "sid": "1CO 15:31"}, "I affirm, by the boasting in you which I have in Masih Isa our Lord, I die daily.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "32", "sid": "1CO 15:32"}, "If I fought with animals at Ephesus for human purposes, what does it profit me? If the dead are not raised, then \u201clet\u2019s\neat and drink, for tomorrow we die.\u201d", {"type": "note", "marker": "x", "content": [{"type": "char", "marker": "xo", "content": ["15:32 "]}, {"type": "char", "marker": "xt", "content": ["Isaiah 22:13"]}], "caller": "+"}, "\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "33", "sid": "1CO 15:33"}, "Don\u2019t be deceived! \u201cEvil companionships corrupt good morals.\u201d\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "34", "sid": "1CO 15:34"}, "Wake up righteously, and don\u2019t sin, for some have no knowledge of Allah. I say this to your shame.\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "35", "sid": "1CO 15:35"}, "But someone will say, \u201cHow are the dead raised?\u201d and, \u201cWith what kind of body do they come?\u201d\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "36", "sid": "1CO 15:36"}, "You foolish one, that which you yourself sow is not made alive unless it dies.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "37", "sid": "1CO 15:37"}, "That which you sow, you don\u2019t sow the body that will be, but a bare grain, maybe of wheat, or of some other kind.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "38", "sid": "1CO 15:38"}, "But Allah gives it a body even as it pleased him, and to each seed a body of its own.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "39", "sid": "1CO 15:39"}, "All flesh is not the same flesh, but there is one flesh of men, another flesh of animals, another of fish, and another of\nbirds. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "40", "sid": "1CO 15:40"}, "There are also celestial bodies and terrestrial bodies; but the glory of the celestial differs from that of the\nterrestrial. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "41", "sid": "1CO 15:41"}, "There is one glory of the sun, another glory of the moon, and another glory of the stars; for one star differs from\nanother star in glory. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "42", "sid": "1CO 15:42"}, "So also is the resurrection of the dead. The body is sown perishable; it is raised imperishable.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "43", "sid": "1CO 15:43"}, "It is sown in dishonour; it is raised in glory. It is sown in weakness; it is raised in power.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "44", "sid": "1CO 15:44"}, "It is sown a natural body; it is raised a spiritual body. There is a natural body and there is also a spiritual body.\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "45", "sid": "1CO 15:45"}, "So also it is written, \u201cThe first man, Adam, became a living soul.\u201d\n", {"type": "note", "marker": "x", "content": [{"type": "char", "marker": "xo", "content": ["15:45 "]}, {"type": "char", "marker": "xt", "content": ["Genesis 2:7"]}], "caller": "+"}, " The last Adam became a life-giving spirit.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "46", "sid": "1CO 15:46"}, "However that which is spiritual isn\u2019t first, but that which is natural, then that which is spiritual.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "47", "sid": "1CO 15:47"}, "The first man is of the earth, made of dust. The second man is the Lord from heaven.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "48", "sid": "1CO 15:48"}, "As is the one made of dust, such are those who are also made of dust; and as is the heavenly, such are they also that are\nheavenly. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "49", "sid": "1CO 15:49"}, "As we have borne the image of those made of dust, let\u2019s", {"type": "note", "marker": "f", "content": [" \n", {"type": "char", "marker": "fr", "content": ["15:49 "]}, {"type": "char", "marker": "ft", "content": ["NU, TR read \u201cwe will\u201d instead of \u201clet\u2019s\u201d"]}], "caller": "+"}, " also bear the image of the heavenly.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "50", "sid": "1CO 15:50"}, "Now I say this, brothers,", {"type": "note", "marker": "f", "content": ["  ", {"type": "char", "marker": "fr", "content": ["15:50 "]}, {"type": "char", "marker": "ft", "content": ["The word for \u201cbrothers\u201d here and where context allows may also be correctly\ntranslated \u201cbrothers and sisters\u201d or \u201csiblings.\u201d"]}], "caller": "+"}, " that flesh and blood can\u2019t inherit Allah\u2019s Kingdom; neither does the\nperishable inherit imperishable. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "51", "sid": "1CO 15:51"}, "Behold,", {"type": "note", "marker": "f", "content": ["  ", {"type": "char", "marker": "fr", "content": ["15:51 "]}, {"type": "char", "marker": "ft", "content": ["\u201cBehold\u201d, from \u201c\u1f30\u03b4\u03bf\u1f7a\u201d, means look at, take notice, observe, see, or gaze at. It is often used\nas an interjection."]}], "caller": "+"}, " I tell you a mystery. We will not all sleep, but we will all be changed,\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "52", "sid": "1CO 15:52"}, "in a moment, in the twinkling of an eye, at the last trumpet. For the trumpet will sound and the dead will be raised\nincorruptible, and we will be changed. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "53", "sid": "1CO 15:53"}, "For this perishable body must become imperishable, and this mortal must put on immortality.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "54", "sid": "1CO 15:54"}, "But when this perishable body will have become imperishable, and this mortal will have put on immortality, then what is\nwritten will happen: \u201cDeath is swallowed up in victory.\u201d", {"type": "note", "marker": "x", "content": [{"type": "char", "marker": "xo", "content": ["15:54\n"]}, {"type": "char", "marker": "xt", "content": ["Isaiah 25:8"]}], "caller": "+"}, " \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "55", "sid": "1CO 15:55"}, "\u201cDeath, where is your sting? \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["Hades,", {"type": "note", "marker": "f", "content": ["  ", {"type": "char", "marker": "fr", "content": ["15:55 "]}, {"type": "char", "marker": "ft", "content": ["or, Hell"]}], "caller": "+"}, " where is your victory?\u201d", {"type": "note", "marker": "x", "content": [{"type": "char", "marker": "xo", "content": ["15:55 "]}, {"type": "char", "marker": "xt", "content": ["See Hosea 13:14"]}], "caller": "+"}, " \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "56", "sid": "1CO 15:56"}, "The sting of death is sin, and the power of sin is the law.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "57", "sid": "1CO 15:57"}, "But thanks be to Allah, who gives us the victory through our Lord Al Masih Isa.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "58", "sid": "1CO 15:58"}, "Therefore, my beloved brothers, be steadfast, immovable, always abounding in the Lord\u2019s work, because you know that your\nlabour is not in vain in the Lord. \n"]}, {"type": "chapter", "marker": "c", "number": "16", "sid": "1CO 16"}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "1", "sid": "1CO 16:1"}, "Now concerning the collection for the saints, as I commanded the assemblies of Galatia, you do likewise.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "2", "sid": "1CO 16:2"}, "On the first day of every week, let each one of you save, as he may prosper, that no collections are made when I come.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "3", "sid": "1CO 16:3"}, "When I arrive, I will send whoever you approve with letters to carry your gracious gift to Jerusalem.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "4", "sid": "1CO 16:4"}, "If it is appropriate for me to go also, they will go with me.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "5", "sid": "1CO 16:5"}, "But I will come to you when I have passed through Macedonia, for I am passing through Macedonia.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "6", "sid": "1CO 16:6"}, "But with you it may be that I will stay, or even winter, that you may send me on my journey wherever I go.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "7", "sid": "1CO 16:7"}, "For I do not wish to see you now in passing, but I hope to stay a while with you, if the Lord permits.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "8", "sid": "1CO 16:8"}, "But I will stay at Ephesus until Pentecost, \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "9", "sid": "1CO 16:9"}, "for a great and effective door has opened to me, and there are many adversaries.\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "10", "sid": "1CO 16:10"}, "Now if Timothy comes, see that he is with you without fear, for he does the work of the Lord, as I also do.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "11", "sid": "1CO 16:11"}, "Therefore let no one despise him. But set him forward on his journey in peace, that he may come to me; for I expect him\nwith the brothers. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "12", "sid": "1CO 16:12"}, "Now concerning Apollos, the brother, I strongly urged him to come to you with the brothers; and it was not at all his\ndesire to come now; but he will come when he has an opportunity.\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "13", "sid": "1CO 16:13"}, "Watch! Stand firm in the faith! Be courageous! Be strong! \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "14", "sid": "1CO 16:14"}, "Let all that you do be done in love. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "15", "sid": "1CO 16:15"}, "Now I beg you, brothers\u2014you know the house of Stephanas, that it is the first fruits of Achaia, and that they have set\nthemselves to serve the saints\u2014 \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "16", "sid": "1CO 16:16"}, "that you also be in subjection to such, and to everyone who helps in the work and labours.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "17", "sid": "1CO 16:17"}, "I rejoice at the coming of Stephanas, Fortunatus, and Achaicus; for that which was lacking on your part, they supplied.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "18", "sid": "1CO 16:18"}, "For they refreshed my spirit and yours. Therefore acknowledge those who are like that.\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "19", "sid": "1CO 16:19"}, "The assemblies of Asia greet you. Aquila and Priscilla greet you much in the Lord, together with the assembly that is in\ntheir house. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "20", "sid": "1CO 16:20"}, "All the brothers greet you. Greet one another with a holy kiss.\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "21", "sid": "1CO 16:21"}, "This greeting is by me, Paul, with my own hand. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "22", "sid": "1CO 16:22"}, "If any man doesn\u2019t love the Lord Al Masih Isa, let him be cursed.\n", {"type": "note", "marker": "f", "content": ["  ", {"type": "char", "marker": "fr", "content": ["16:22 "]}, {"type": "char", "marker": "ft", "content": ["Greek: anathema."]}], "caller": "+"}, " Come, Lord!", {"type": "note", "marker": "f", "content": ["  ", {"type": "char", "marker": "fr", "content": ["16:22\n"]}, {"type": "char", "marker": "ft", "content": ["Aramaic: Maranatha!"]}], "caller": "+"}, " \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "23", "sid": "1CO 16:23"}, "The grace of the Lord Al Masih Isa be with you. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "24", "sid": "1CO 16:24"}, "My love to all of you in Masih Isa. Amen. "]}]}